outlooksByWeek.1: Patrick Mahomes is coming off his least productive NFL season in 2024, passing for 3,928 yards over 16 regular-season games on 6.8 yards per attempt with 26 touchdown passes, all career lows. Kansas City's front office has invested draft capital in trying to give the QB the weapons necessary to revive the passing game, but while 2024 first-round pick Xavier Worthy showed flashes of upside and game-breaking speed, 2023 second-round pick Rashee Rice played only four games last year due to a knee injury and is set to miss the first six in 2025 due to a suspension. Mahomes' veteran partner in crime, tight end Travis Kelce, also saw his yards per target crater in 2024 as the 35-year-old enters the twilight of his career. Mahomes and company will head to Sao Paulo in Week 1 to take on the Chargers, whose defense finished in the top 10 in fewest passing yards allowed and most interceptions last year.
outlooksByWeek.2: Patrick Mahomes posted respectable numbers in Week 1 despite more attrition in Kansas City's wide receiver corps. The veteran quarterback threw for 258 yards and a touchdown while adding another 57 yards and a TD on the ground, but he watched Xavier Worthy leave the game with a shoulder injury after a collision with Travis Kelce. Worthy joins a suspended Rashee Rice on the sidelines, and while he may avoid surgery for his dislocated shoulder, he's almost certain to miss some time while rehabbing and adjusting to wearing a brace. Mahomes will try to make do with a patchwork group of targets led by Kelce and Hollywood Brown in Week 2 against an Eagles defense that held Dak Prescott and the Cowboys' passing game in check in its opener, and which ranked second in passing yards allowed in 2024.
outlooksByWeek.3: Patrick Mahomes produced one passing and one rushing touchdown in each of Kansas City's first two games, but his passing yardage and completion percentage are both below his usual rates while the team deals with multiple absences in its receiving corps. The veteran quarterback showed some chemistry with Hollywood Brown in Week 1 and found Tyquan Thornton for a deep TD in Week 2, but that hasn't been enough to get the team into the win column. Xavier Worthy could return for a Week 3 contest against the Giants, but he's unlikely to be 100% as he attempts to play through a shoulder injury. After facing two tough defenses to begin the year, Mahomes should have an easier time against a Giants unit that just surrendered 361 passing yards to Dak Prescott in an OT loss to the Cowboys.
outlooksByWeek.4: Patrick Mahomes is struggling to find his MVP form. Through three games, the Kansas City quarterback has yet to reach 260 passing yards or a 62 percent completion rate, and he hasn't thrown multiple TDs in any contest. A shorthanded wide receiver group is a big part of the problem, and while Mahomes has begun to establish some chemistry with Tyquan Thornton, Xavier Worthy remains sidelined with a shoulder injury and Rashee Rice won't be bad from his suspension until Week 7. Worthy could return in Week 4, but even if he does he could be limited by the harness he'll be forced to wear, Mahomes will try to take advantage of Week 4's clash with a Ravens defense that ranks 28th in passing yards allowed so far this season.
outlooksByWeek.5: Patrick Mahomes is coming off his most productive game in nearly two years. The Kansas City superstar threw four TD passes in a big Week 4 win over the Ravens, the first time he's tossed more than three since Week 7 of the 2023 season. His 270 passing yards and 7.3 yards per attempt were also season highs, and the return of wideout Xavier Worthy was a big factor in the passing game springing to life. Rashee Rice's pending return from suspension in Week 7 should provide the offense with a further boost. Mahomes aims to maintain his momentum in Week 5 against an aggressive Jaguars defense ranking first in the league in QB rating against thanks to nine interceptions, but only 12th in fantasy points per game allowed to QB.
outlooksByWeek.6: Patrick Mahomes completed 29 of 41 pass attempts for 318 yards, one touchdown and one interception while taking six carries for 60 yards and another score in Week 5's Monday night's 31-28 loss to the Jaguars. Even though he couldn't lead the Chiefs to a win, Mahomes surpassed the 300-yard mark for the first time in 2025, and he's now tossed at least 270 passing yards in his last two outings. He's trending in the right direction, but Mahomes needs to be at his best in Week 6 when the Chiefs face a middle-of-the-pack Lions defense in terms of fantasy points allowed to QBs.
outlooksByWeek.7: Patrick Mahomes appears to be rounding into MVP form. The Kansas City superstar set season highs with a 73.3% completion rate and 8.6 yards per attempt in a Week 6 win over the Lions, and over the last three games he's delivered an 8:1 TD:INT while also running in two scores. That strong stretch could be just a prelude for a big second half of 2025, as Rashee Rice is set to make his season debut after serving out his six-game suspension. Mahomes won't have a premium matchup in Week 7 against a Raiders defense that ranks 19th in passing yards allowed but is tied for 12th in fantasy points per game allowed to QB.
outlooksByWeek.8: Patrick Mahomes enjoyed having Rashee Rice back in the fold in Kansas City's Week 7 rout of the Raiders, as Mahomes threw at least three touchdown passes for the third time in the last four games. Over that stretch, the quarterback has a 71.3% completion rate, 7.9 YPA and 11:1 TD:INT. Mahomes' impressive passing numbers come as the Chiefs struggle putting together an effective running attack, which could lead to even more passing volume in more competitive contests. Mahomes figures to post strong numbers again in Week 8 against a Commanders defense that ranks 23rd in fantasy points per game allowed to QB and 32nd in yards per attempt allowed.
outlooksByWeek.9: Patrick Mahomes continues to light up secondaries, throwing at least three touchdowns for the third straight game and the fourth time in Kansas City's last five contests in a Week 8 win over Washington. The star QB has also topped a 70% completion rate in four straight starts, and during that five-game stretch he's compiled 1,430 passing yards, a 71.8% completion rate, 8.1 yards per attempt and a 14:3 TD:INT while also chipping in two rushing TDs. Mahomes' surge has been boosted by the returns of Xavier Worthy from a shoulder injury and Rashee Rice from suspension, and the latter has caught three scores in two games since being added back to the roster. Mahomes will need to stay sharp in Week 9 during a clash of AFC powerhouses, as he faces a Bills defense that ranks second in fantasy points per game allowed to QBs in 2025.

player.seasonOutlook: Mahomes enters his age-29 season no longer an elite fantasy option, but rather a solid mid-to-back-end starter. After five straight seasons as a top-6 fantasy QB (PPG), he's finished 13th and 11th the past two seasons. Mahomes has evolved into a quarterback who still attempts a ton of passes (exactly third in pass attempts four years in a row), but is more conservative (career-low 6.4 aDOT and 6.8 YPA in 2024) and doesn't throw as many TDs as in years past (26 last season was his fewest since 2019). Perhaps he'll rebound a bit in that area with the Xavier Worthy/Rashee Rice/Hollywood Brown trio together, but in the meantime Mahomes adds just enough with his legs (between 300 and 400 yards five seasons in a row) to keep him in the fantasy starter conversation.
